    "body": "I can't reproduce this with plain calls. Please check this and see if it happens to you:\r\n\r\n1. Run `npx hardhat node --url ALCHEMY_URL`\r\n2. In another terminal, run this sequence of commands:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"eth_blockNumber\",\"params\":[]}' -H 'Content-Type:application/json' http://localhost:8545\r\ncurl -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"hardhat_reset\",\"params\":[{\"forking\": {\"jsonRpcUrl\": \"ALCHEMY_URL\", \"blockNumber\": 12330245}}]}' -H 'Content-Type:application/json' http://localhost:8545\r\ncurl -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"eth_blockNumber\",\"params\":[]}' -H 'Content-Type:application/json' http://localhost:8545\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe first command should return the current mainnet block number, the second one should return true, and the third one should return `0xbc2505`.\r\n\r\nIf this works for you, then you might have a problem with your code, or there might be an issue in the web3 library you are using.",
